# Git shipping (local merge → push)

**Owner workflow:** open a local feature branch → finish work → merge into local `main` → `git push origin main` (or ask the user to push). Do **not** use GitHub PR as the default path.

## Forbidden unless the user explicitly asks in this thread

- `gh pr create` / opening a GitHub Pull Request
- Enabling GitHub auto-merge / squash-merge into `main`
- Pushing or merging **to `origin/main`** from a Cloud/Background Agent
- Pushing remote feature branches solely so Actions/Cursor can open a PR

## Cloud / Background Agents

If running in Cursor Cloud: leave changes on a feature branch and stop. Do **not** merge to `main`, do **not** open a PR, do **not** push `main`. Report the branch name and wait for the human to merge locally and push.

## Still allowed without extra ask

- Local commits on a feature branch
- Local `git merge` into local `main` when the user asked to land the change that way
- Pushing `main` only when the user explicitly says push / `pnpm push` / ship
